                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d44">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">832.5151/129: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-03-28T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 28, 1933—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>45. Information has reached the Department through an apparently reliable channel
                    that a special Rothschild representative reached Rio March 10, and would soon
                    present a plan “for the settlement of Brazil’s foreign debts in Europe”.</p>
                <p>Please cable verification and all obtainable pertinent information. Indicate, if
                    possible, (<hi rend="italic">a</hi>) whether any special favors to British
                    interests in allotment of exchange are involved and (<hi rend="italic">b</hi>)
                    whether any other agreement is being simultaneously negotiated which would
                    affect commerce between Brazil and Great Britain.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
